ctive_lock_reason": null, "body": "I think this is hard to fix in general, but worth a report nevertheless, even if only as an FYI to everyone who also is toying around with [try.gogs.io](https://try.gogs.io): It seems that I ran out of space on try.gogs.io, but it took me a while to figure this out.\r\nThe HTTPResponse of the try.gogs.io instance was only reported with increased logging, and the rendered Error message was quite unhelpful.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$  datalad create-sibling-gogs -d . datalad --credential gogs-datalad2 --api \"https://try.gogs.io\"             1 !\r\nAn access token is required for https://try.gogs.io. Visit https://try.gogs.io/user/settings/applications to create a token\r\ntoken: \r\n[ERROR  ] HTTPError(500 Server Error: Internal Server Error for url: https://try.gogs.io/api/v1/user/repos) (HTTPError) \r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the debug log I found:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[DEBUG  ] GOGS responded with <Response [500]> {'message': \"initRepository: createDelegateHooks: create delegate hook '/home/git/gogs-repositories/adswa/datalad.git/hooks/post-receive': open /home/git/gogs-repositories/adswa/datalad.git/hooks/post-receive: no space left on device\", 'url': 'https://github.com/gogs/docs-api'} \r\n[ERROR  ] HTTPError(500 Server Error: Internal Server Error for url: https://try.gogs.io/api/v1/user/repos) (HTTPError) \r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/subscriptions